    "ts": "2026-04-27T13:58:05+00:00",
    "headline": "Adidas shares rise after 'supershoe' helps seal sub-two hour marathon win",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: Adidas shares rose on Monday (April 27) the day after a historic racing win.</p><p>Investors bought in after Kenya's Sabastian Sawe became the first person to run a marathon in under two hours in an official race.</p><p>He won the London Marathon wearing Adidas' Adizero Adios Pro Evo 3 trainers.</p><p>Sawe finished the race in one hour 59 minutes and 30 seconds.</p><p>The sub‑two‑hour marathon has been one of sport's biggest goals for years.</p><p>Ethiopia's Yomif Kejelcha finished second in his marathon debut on Sunday.</p><p>While Tigst Assefa broke her own women-only world record.</p><p>All three were wearing the same make of Adidas trainers, which are due to go on sale on Thursday for a reported $500.</p><p>The win is a boost for Adidas against arch-rival Nike.</p><p>It comes after years of lab‑backed experiments and near‑misses looking to build a so-called \"supershoe\" to break the record.</p><p>Nike's Breaking2 attempt at Monza in 2017 just fell short.</p><p>Although Kenyan great Eliud Kipchoge ran under two hours in INEOS's 1:59 Challenge two years later.</p><p>But those efforts fell outside the sport's official record books.</p><p>Adidas said the Pro Evo 3 weighs an average 30% less than its predecessor and improves running economy by 1.6%.</p><p>Adidas shares were up 2% in mid-morning trade, although they're down close to a fifth since the start of this year.</p><p>That's due to concerns about the group's exposure to U.S. tariffs and the impact of the Middle East conflict.</p></body>",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/video/adidas-shares-rise-supershoe-helps-135805920.html",
    "source": "Reuters Videos",
    "provider": "yfinance",
    "raw": {
